  "body": "Solidity 0.8.4 has introduced \"Custom Errors\", which are error messages encoded with a signature & data, similar to function calls.\r\n\r\nhttps://blog.soliditylang.org/2021/04/21/custom-errors/\r\n\r\nHowever, Hardhat currently tries to decode all revert data as a string. If custom errors are used, it will throw the following error:\r\n\r\n```\r\nError: Number can only safely store up to 53 bits\r\n    at assert (node_modules/bn.js/lib/bn.js:6:21)\r\n    at BN.toNumber (node_modules/bn.js/lib/bn.js:519:7)\r\n    at decodeSingle (node_modules/ethereumjs-abi/lib/index.js:243:52)\r\n    at decodeSingle (node_modules/ethereumjs-abi/lib/index.js:223:17)\r\n    at Function.ABI.rawDecode (node_modules/ethereumjs-abi/lib/index.js:390:19)\r\n    at Object.decodeRevertReason (node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/stack-traces/revert-reasons.ts:10:19)\r\n    at HardhatNode._manageErrors (node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/node.ts:1206:8)\r\n    at HardhatNode._gatherTraces (node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/node.ts:937:12)\r\n```\r\n\r\nHardhat should parse Error definitions from the contract's ABI and parse \"Custom Errors\" correctly.",
